WEBVTT

1
00:01:01.955 --> 00:01:03.624
Man: Police found her in the street.

2
00:01:03.707 --> 00:01:06.376
Looks like she was bitten
by some kind of an animal.

3
00:01:06.460 --> 00:01:10.714
Woman: Jesus. Her water's broken.
She's going into uterine contractions.

4
00:01:10.797 --> 00:01:12.382
We have to do a c-section.

5
00:01:28.941 --> 00:01:30.359
[Baby crying]

6
00:01:30.442 --> 00:01:32.819
[EKG flatlining]

7
00:02:10.732 --> 00:02:13.944
- What you got down there, little man?
- That's my heat-seeker.

8
00:02:14.027 --> 00:02:15.279
I'll bet it is.

9
00:02:16.280 --> 00:02:17.531
[Squeals]

10
00:02:17.614 --> 00:02:18.740
[Laughs]

11
00:02:18.824 --> 00:02:21.951
- So where we going?
- It's a surprise, baby.

12
00:02:22.035 --> 00:02:26.248
Yeah, I like surprises. Yeah.

13
00:02:29.835 --> 00:02:31.795
Oh, my god.

14
00:02:32.671 --> 00:02:34.506
What the fuck are we doing here?

15
00:02:36.508 --> 00:02:38.927
Whoo. Look at all that.

16
00:02:39.011 --> 00:02:40.804
[Laughs]

17
00:02:41.346 --> 00:02:43.473
What the fuck is that?

18
00:02:49.813 --> 00:02:51.148
Hey.

19
00:02:51.231 --> 00:02:53.775
[Speaking in foreign language]

20
00:02:53.859 --> 00:02:56.153
What did you just say?

21
00:03:04.661 --> 00:03:07.831
[Dance music playing over speakers]

22
00:03:34.316 --> 00:03:35.442
Wow.

23
00:03:50.916 --> 00:03:54.920
Hey, what's up? Oh, man.

24
00:04:03.136 --> 00:04:06.640
Whoo! All right.

25
00:04:13.355 --> 00:04:16.983
Yeah. Whoo!

26
00:04:28.120 --> 00:04:30.163
[Laughing]

27
00:04:31.289 --> 00:04:33.333
What's happening?

28
00:04:33.417 --> 00:04:35.293
[Grunts]

29
00:04:41.675 --> 00:04:42.801
Hey, man.

30
00:04:48.515 --> 00:04:50.142
Fuck.

31
00:04:59.818 --> 00:05:02.571
Fuck, I need a drink.

32
00:05:50.076 --> 00:05:51.411
No. No.

33
00:05:57.292 --> 00:05:58.626
What's wrong, baby?

34
00:05:58.710 --> 00:06:00.086
[Hisses]

35
00:06:00.170 --> 00:06:03.089
[Screaming]

36
00:06:03.173 --> 00:06:04.633
No!

37
00:06:04.716 --> 00:06:07.093
[Growling and hissing]

38
00:06:09.513 --> 00:06:10.597
Oh, no.

39
00:06:33.995 --> 00:06:36.873
Man 1: Shut up, man.

40
00:06:55.684 --> 00:06:58.562
- Woman: Is that him?
- Man 2: Jesus, it's him.

41
00:07:00.063 --> 00:07:01.356
Man 3: It's the day Walker.

42
00:07:22.752 --> 00:07:25.213
Come on, day Walker!

43
00:07:25.297 --> 00:07:27.257
[Vampires screaming]

44
00:07:30.135 --> 00:07:31.803
[Screaming]

45
00:07:45.150 --> 00:07:48.653
Hey! I'm gonna rip
your fucking head off.

46
00:08:05.670 --> 00:08:08.632
- Look out! Hey, out of the way!
- Get out of there!

47
00:08:42.165 --> 00:08:46.044
That's him. That's him.
Get him. Fuck him up.

48
00:08:46.127 --> 00:08:51.341
We're gonna Jack you up.
Make him hurt bad. Whoo!

49
00:09:39.222 --> 00:09:40.849
[Yelling]

50
00:09:44.144 --> 00:09:47.564
[Quinn speaking in foreign language]

51
00:09:54.779 --> 00:09:56.531
Quinn...

52
00:09:58.908 --> 00:10:01.619
I'm getting a little tired
of chopping you up.

53
00:10:05.540 --> 00:10:09.210
Thought I might try fire, for a change.

54
00:10:12.047 --> 00:10:14.174
Give my regards to frost.

55
00:10:17.635 --> 00:10:20.013
No, please. Please don't.

56
00:10:21.055 --> 00:10:22.135
Man 1: Over here, sergeant.

57
00:10:34.110 --> 00:10:35.487
- Put him out.
- Yes, sir.

58
00:10:35.570 --> 00:10:37.655
Man 2: Paramedics, coming through.

59
00:11:00.178 --> 00:11:03.807
Got a charred cadaver here for you.
It's still warm too.

60
00:11:03.890 --> 00:11:05.391
One, two, three.

61
00:11:10.980 --> 00:11:13.399
Oh, Jesus, that's rank.

62
00:11:13.483 --> 00:11:16.694
Man: Paramedics said he was
still screaming when they found him...

63
00:11:16.778 --> 00:11:19.322
Stapled to a wall.

64
00:11:19.405 --> 00:11:21.699
Curtis: That's very pretty.

65
00:11:34.379 --> 00:11:38.091
Curtis: Did you check the chem panel?
Blood sugar's three times the norm.

66
00:11:38.174 --> 00:11:40.343
Phosphorus and uric acid
are off the charts.

67
00:11:40.426 --> 00:11:42.679
Karen: You took this off a doa?

68
00:11:43.721 --> 00:11:45.305
Yeah.

69
00:11:45.974 --> 00:11:47.684
But this doesn't make any sense.

70
00:11:51.563 --> 00:11:54.107
The red blood cells are biconvex,
which is impossible.

71
00:11:54.649 --> 00:11:57.527
Look at the polys, they're binucleated.

72
00:12:00.613 --> 00:12:04.909
- Okay, Curtis, it's 3:00 in the morning...
- This is not a joke.

73
00:12:04.993 --> 00:12:08.246
I've got the body sitting in the morgue
right now.

74
00:12:09.038 --> 00:12:11.875
I thought you promised
to give me some distance.

75
00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:14.627
I just want you to come down
and take a look.

76
00:12:21.467 --> 00:12:24.888
Okay. Show me the body.

77
00:12:24.971 --> 00:12:27.223
And I don't wanna hear
a word about us.

78
00:12:27.307 --> 00:12:30.727
Done. We've had that conversation.

79
00:12:34.022 --> 00:12:36.316
You haven't started
on the internal organs yet?

80
00:12:36.399 --> 00:12:39.569
No, just a blood sample
through the pericardium.

81
00:12:40.904 --> 00:12:44.240
The maxilla looks a little deformed.

82
00:12:44.324 --> 00:12:46.910
There's some odd muscle structure
around the canines.

83
00:12:46.993 --> 00:12:49.996
I'm gonna go ahead start the y
and check the tracheal mucosa.

84
00:12:55.043 --> 00:12:57.462
Let me ask you something.

85
00:12:58.338 --> 00:13:00.256
Honestly.

86
00:13:01.007 --> 00:13:03.551
You ever have second thoughts
about us?

87
00:13:05.887 --> 00:13:06.930
Sometimes.

88
00:13:09.140 --> 00:13:11.768
But then I remember
how much of an asshole you were.

89
00:13:11.851 --> 00:13:13.561
You wanna cut me some slack here?

90
00:13:13.645 --> 00:13:16.314
You asked for some time off,
I gave you some time off.

91
00:13:16.397 --> 00:13:18.775
- Look, Curtis, it's over.
- I'm trying. Really, I am.

92
00:13:18.858 --> 00:13:20.652
[Gasping]

93
00:13:38.795 --> 00:13:41.839
- Man 1: Call security!
- Man 2: Get back!

94
00:13:56.813 --> 00:13:58.523
Came back to finish you off.

95
00:13:58.606 --> 00:14:00.483
Get out of my way, you freak.

96
00:14:07.699 --> 00:14:09.075
Freeze!

97
00:14:10.952 --> 00:14:13.621
Motherfucker,
are you out of your damn mind?

98
00:14:22.755 --> 00:14:25.174
[Screaming]

99
00:15:04.130 --> 00:15:06.066
- Man 1: He's there, right there.
- Man 2: Go ahead.

100
00:15:06.090 --> 00:15:07.675
- Go.
- Man 3: Hey, you, freeze.

101
00:15:07.759 --> 00:15:09.359
- Man 4: Come on. Come on.
- Man 5: Fire.

102
00:15:10.678 --> 00:15:11.887
Man 6: Keep going. Keep going.

103
00:15:14.724 --> 00:15:16.517
Man 7: Come back out.

104
00:15:17.393 --> 00:15:19.395
- Man 3: Go.
- Man 7: He can't get out.

105
00:15:20.563 --> 00:15:22.607
[Screaming]

106
00:15:26.527 --> 00:15:28.653
- Freeze!
- Man 1: Hold it right there.

107
00:15:28.738 --> 00:15:30.823
- Man 2: Don't do it.
- Man 3: Hey, hey...

108
00:15:44.587 --> 00:15:46.214
Karen: My shoulder...

109
00:15:46.631 --> 00:15:48.883
Is dislocated.

110
00:15:50.843 --> 00:15:52.220
[Yells]

111
00:17:32.778 --> 00:17:35.198
[Machinery buzzing]

112
00:17:35.281 --> 00:17:37.658
[Over speakers]
I feel rivers overflowing.

113
00:17:37.742 --> 00:17:39.619
Blade: Whistler.

114
00:17:42.663 --> 00:17:44.123
Whistler.

115
00:17:46.292 --> 00:17:47.960
[Music stops]

116
00:17:50.046 --> 00:17:51.631
Whistler: Bringing home strays now?

117
00:17:54.175 --> 00:17:55.343
She's been bitten.

118
00:17:59.764 --> 00:18:01.516
Should've killed her, then.

119
00:18:01.599 --> 00:18:03.601
Yeah, I know...

120
00:18:05.478 --> 00:18:06.979
But I didn't.

121
00:18:13.778 --> 00:18:18.991
You watch her close.
She starts to turn, you finish her off.

122
00:18:22.995 --> 00:18:24.956
Or I will.

123
00:18:32.046 --> 00:18:33.631
She's borderline.

124
00:18:35.466 --> 00:18:39.136
Another hour,
she'd be well into the change.

125
00:18:40.721 --> 00:18:44.308
Dr. Karen jenson, listen close.

126
00:18:44.642 --> 00:18:49.063
I'm gonna inject you
with allium sativum. Garlic.

127
00:18:49.146 --> 00:18:51.232
This is gonna hurt a lot.

128
00:18:51.315 --> 00:18:53.276
It was Quinn.

129
00:18:53.359 --> 00:18:55.945
Frost's little errand boy?

130
00:18:56.445 --> 00:18:59.031
- You get a lead on him?
- No.

131
00:18:59.991 --> 00:19:01.701
Whistler: Too bad.

132
00:19:03.369 --> 00:19:04.453
[Grunts]

133
00:19:04.537 --> 00:19:06.455
Hold her.

134
00:19:16.632 --> 00:19:21.345
I give her fifty-fifty,
if she makes it through the night.

135
00:19:47.455 --> 00:19:51.125
Blade, the day Walker.

136
00:19:51.208 --> 00:19:53.794
Still pursuing his ridiculous crusade.

137
00:19:57.590 --> 00:19:59.634
How many died?

138
00:20:00.092 --> 00:20:04.722
We don't have an exact count.
Apparently, he used a lot of silver.

139
00:20:05.556 --> 00:20:08.351
- We're having difficulty...
- Send in frost.

140
00:20:16.692 --> 00:20:17.777
Deacon frost.

141
00:20:21.781 --> 00:20:24.075
You can come in now.

142
00:20:33.209 --> 00:20:37.380
[In foreign language]

143
00:20:58.109 --> 00:21:00.152
These nightclubs of yours
are dangerous.

144
00:21:00.236 --> 00:21:01.987
Are they?

145
00:21:02.071 --> 00:21:05.783
They draw needless attention
to our kind. You know our policy.

146
00:21:05.866 --> 00:21:07.868
Your policy, not mine.

147
00:21:08.494 --> 00:21:10.079
Dragonetti: Our livelihood...

148
00:21:10.996 --> 00:21:15.084
Depends on our ability to blend in...

149
00:21:15.334 --> 00:21:16.711
On our discretion.

150
00:21:17.795 --> 00:21:20.965
Maybe it's time
we forgot about discretion.

151
00:21:21.674 --> 00:21:23.426
We should be ruling the humans...

152
00:21:23.509 --> 00:21:26.554
Not running around
making back-alley treaties with them.

153
00:21:26.637 --> 00:21:30.181
For fuck's sake,
these people are our food not our allies.

154
00:21:30.266 --> 00:21:33.102
- You're out of line, frost.
- Am I?

155
00:21:33.185 --> 00:21:36.981
Maybe I'm just the first to say out loud
what we've all been thinking.

156
00:21:37.064 --> 00:21:41.694
We have existed this way
for thousands of years.

157
00:21:41.777 --> 00:21:46.449
Who are you to challenge our ways?

158
00:21:46.532 --> 00:21:48.701
You're not even a pureblood.

159
00:21:52.121 --> 00:21:53.330
Like it matters.

160
00:21:54.623 --> 00:21:58.377
I was born a vampire...

161
00:21:58.461 --> 00:22:02.256
As was every other member
of this house.

162
00:22:02.339 --> 00:22:03.507
But, you, frost...

163
00:22:07.052 --> 00:22:09.555
You were merely turned.

164
00:22:11.682 --> 00:22:15.686
The world belongs to us,
not the humans.

165
00:22:16.020 --> 00:22:18.189
You know that.

166
00:22:22.150 --> 00:22:24.986
Do we have any other business
to discuss?

167
00:22:25.821 --> 00:22:30.201
Well, there's the matter of our offshore
accounts. We're having difficulty...

168
00:22:30.284 --> 00:22:31.994
And have you made the transfer...?

169
00:22:32.077 --> 00:22:37.416
Gaetano, you may wake up one day
and find yourself extinct.

170
00:22:49.220 --> 00:22:50.805
[Bell rings]

171
00:23:10.533 --> 00:23:14.161
- You're a week early.
- Yeah.

172
00:23:20.876 --> 00:23:24.964
Whistler says I'm building up
a resistance to the serum.

173
00:23:26.799 --> 00:23:29.218
Yeah, I figured that might happen.

174
00:23:38.435 --> 00:23:40.729
You take care, all right?

175
00:25:24.917 --> 00:25:27.544
Whistler: I must be getting soft
in my old age...

176
00:25:27.628 --> 00:25:30.506
Letting you bring home
a stray like that.

177
00:25:31.173 --> 00:25:36.095
It was damn stupid of you.
You might have lucked out though.

178
00:25:37.054 --> 00:25:39.306
I checked her background.

179
00:25:42.017 --> 00:25:45.269
Turns out she's a hematologist.

180
00:25:45.980 --> 00:25:48.732
She might be useful to us.

181
00:25:49.650 --> 00:25:51.527
Blade: I doubt it.

182
00:25:52.569 --> 00:25:54.196
Whistler: I'm serious.

183
00:25:54.279 --> 00:25:59.326
I took a look at that notebook of hers.
She's on to something.

184
00:26:01.245 --> 00:26:02.705
I had to increase the dose.

185
00:26:04.248 --> 00:26:07.626
It's over 50 milligrams now.
That's getting dangerous.

186
00:26:07.710 --> 00:26:12.172
Just do it, old man.

187
00:27:11.732 --> 00:27:13.692
Wander off the beaten path, doctor?

188
00:27:15.611 --> 00:27:17.488
Who are you people?

189
00:27:17.571 --> 00:27:18.989
My name's Abraham whistler.

190
00:27:20.449 --> 00:27:21.742
You've met blade.

191
00:27:38.008 --> 00:27:39.802
So am I a prisoner here?

192
00:27:41.303 --> 00:27:43.305
Not at all.

193
00:27:43.388 --> 00:27:47.559
We just had to take certain precautions
before we let you go.

194
00:27:48.060 --> 00:27:51.063
You gotta understand,
they're everywhere.

195
00:27:51.146 --> 00:27:53.065
Vampires.

196
00:27:53.148 --> 00:27:54.775
The hominis nocturna.

197
00:27:56.068 --> 00:27:57.694
We hunt them, you see.

198
00:27:57.778 --> 00:28:01.448
Moving from one city to the next
tracking their migrations.

199
00:28:01.532 --> 00:28:02.866
They're hard to kill.

200
00:28:02.950 --> 00:28:06.620
- They tend to regenerate.
- And I'm supposed to believe all this?

201
00:28:06.703 --> 00:28:09.790
Well, you already met Mr. Crispy
at the hospital.

202
00:28:09.873 --> 00:28:11.458
What do you think?

203
00:28:13.961 --> 00:28:17.464
So, what do you use, then?
Stakes? Crosses?

204
00:28:17.548 --> 00:28:22.344
Crosses don't do squat.
Some of the legends are true, though.

205
00:28:22.427 --> 00:28:26.223
Vampires are severely allergic to silver.

206
00:28:26.306 --> 00:28:29.184
Feed them garlic
and they go into anaphylactic shock.

207
00:28:29.268 --> 00:28:32.646
Then, of course, there's always sunlight,
ultraviolet rays.

208
00:28:33.939 --> 00:28:38.318
I got this sucker running.
You wanna give it a try tonight?

209
00:28:44.283 --> 00:28:45.701
Still heavy.

210
00:28:47.119 --> 00:28:48.537
But you're so big.

211
00:28:51.081 --> 00:28:54.626
If you wanna live to see another day,
you'll be out of town by nightfall.

212
00:28:54.710 --> 00:28:56.461
So where am I supposed to go?

213
00:29:00.299 --> 00:29:02.801
You've been exposed to them.

214
00:29:03.051 --> 00:29:06.722
One way or another,
somebody's gonna take you out.

215
00:29:10.934 --> 00:29:13.645
There's a war going on out there.

216
00:29:14.188 --> 00:29:16.982
Blade, myself, a few others...

217
00:29:17.065 --> 00:29:20.235
We've tried to keep it
from spilling over onto the streets...

218
00:29:20.319 --> 00:29:24.740
But sometimes, people like yourself
get caught in the crossfire.

219
00:29:24.823 --> 00:29:27.534
I have blood samples.
I can go to the police.

220
00:29:27.618 --> 00:29:30.162
They own the police.

221
00:29:30.245 --> 00:29:32.830
You have to understand,
they're everywhere.

222
00:29:32.915 --> 00:29:35.709
Chances are you've seen them yourself
and didn't know it.

223
00:29:35.792 --> 00:29:37.502
On the subway or in a bar.

224
00:29:39.838 --> 00:29:41.757
So that's it?

225
00:29:42.716 --> 00:29:45.552
You guys just patch me up
and send me on my way.

226
00:29:49.598 --> 00:29:53.560
Here. Vampire mace.

227
00:29:54.478 --> 00:29:56.396
Silver nitrate, essence of garlic.

228
00:29:57.356 --> 00:29:59.107
You keep your eyes open.

229
00:29:59.816 --> 00:30:01.609
Be careful.

230
00:30:05.155 --> 00:30:07.407
One other thing...

231
00:30:07.908 --> 00:30:10.369
Buy yourself a gun.

232
00:30:11.078 --> 00:30:13.288
If you start getting sensitive
to daylight...

233
00:30:14.665 --> 00:30:19.670
If you find you're thirsty, regardless
of how much you've had to drink...

234
00:30:19.962 --> 00:30:24.049
Then I suggest you take that gun
and use it on yourself.

235
00:30:27.219 --> 00:30:30.138
Better that than the alternative.

236
00:31:25.402 --> 00:31:27.362
[Dance music playing on headphones]

237
00:31:27.446 --> 00:31:29.530
You have been warned before.

238
00:31:29.614 --> 00:31:34.119
These archives are restricted
to the members of the house of erebus.

239
00:31:36.121 --> 00:31:40.125
You are wasting your time.
It's a dead language.

240
00:31:40.208 --> 00:31:43.837
The ancient texts
can never be translated.

241
00:31:45.297 --> 00:31:47.465
You wouldn't even understand them.

242
00:31:49.926 --> 00:31:52.137
Damn it, frost, I'm talking to you!

243
00:31:53.138 --> 00:31:56.058
Shh.

244
00:31:56.141 --> 00:31:59.102
Keep your voice down, gaetano.

245
00:31:59.186 --> 00:32:00.520
[Music stops]

246
00:32:00.604 --> 00:32:03.273
We're in a library.
You don't need to shout.

247
00:32:04.733 --> 00:32:07.069
What are you up to, frost?

248
00:32:18.372 --> 00:32:21.291
What are you gonna do? Hm?

249
00:32:26.129 --> 00:32:27.839
What?

250
00:32:32.427 --> 00:32:34.679
You bore me.

251
00:33:09.172 --> 00:33:12.008
Blade: Remember what we told you.

252
00:33:12.092 --> 00:33:15.345
You keep your eyes open.
They're everywhere.

253
00:33:17.305 --> 00:33:18.849
But it's daytime.

254
00:33:25.439 --> 00:33:27.959
- Man 1: Hey, hey, hey, that's mine.
- Man 2: Spare some change?

255
00:33:52.757 --> 00:33:55.385
- Man 3: Anything else?
- Woman: No, that's it.

256
00:34:18.658 --> 00:34:19.868
How you doing?

257
00:35:40.699 --> 00:35:44.411
I'm sorry. Whoa, whoa! Hold on.
