00:58:38.700 --> 00:58:43.789
He can withstand garlic, silver,
even sunlight.

507
00:58:43.872 --> 00:58:45.457
And he's got their strength.

508
00:58:47.542 --> 00:58:50.420
This time tomorrow,
all those wounds of his will be healed.

509
00:58:52.381 --> 00:58:54.925
He still ages like a human, though.

510
00:58:55.008 --> 00:58:57.594
See, vampires age slower than us.

511
00:58:58.804 --> 00:59:04.017
Unfortunately,
he also inherited their thirst.

512
00:59:04.601 --> 00:59:07.688
Karen: I thought the serum
was supposed to suppress that.

513
00:59:07.771 --> 00:59:10.065
Time's running out.

514
00:59:11.441 --> 00:59:14.319
His body's starting to reject it.

515
00:59:14.945 --> 00:59:19.700
So far, all my efforts
to find a cure have failed.

516
00:59:23.578 --> 00:59:25.288
Why do you hunt them?

517
00:59:27.374 --> 00:59:29.835
I had a family once.

518
00:59:29.918 --> 00:59:33.130
A wife, two daughters.

519
00:59:34.965 --> 00:59:38.677
Then a drifter came calling one evening.
A vampire.

520
00:59:40.679 --> 00:59:42.472
He toyed with them first.

521
00:59:43.348 --> 00:59:47.269
Tried to make me decide
which order they'd die in.

522
00:59:50.981 --> 00:59:55.902
We kill as many of them as we can find,
but it's getting worse.

523
00:59:55.986 --> 00:59:57.320
Because of frost.

524
00:59:57.404 --> 01:00:00.907
There's something happening
in the vampire ranks.

525
01:00:00.991 --> 01:00:03.200
It's something big.

526
01:00:03.493 --> 01:00:07.914
And I'd stake my life
that son of a bitch is at the center of it.

527
01:00:11.501 --> 01:00:13.545
Karen: Blade?

528
01:00:30.520 --> 01:00:33.398
Whistler told me what happened.

529
01:00:36.109 --> 01:00:38.945
He told me what you are.

530
01:00:41.698 --> 01:00:43.950
You don't know me.

531
01:00:44.034 --> 01:00:46.870
You don't know anything about me.

532
01:00:49.206 --> 01:00:51.249
I'm not human.

533
01:00:54.544 --> 01:00:55.629
You look human to me...

534
01:00:55.712 --> 01:00:58.590
Humans don't drink blood.

535
01:00:58.673 --> 01:01:01.134
That was a long time ago.

536
01:01:01.968 --> 01:01:04.096
Maybe you should let that go.

537
01:01:06.932 --> 01:01:11.853
I have spent my whole life looking
for that thing that killed my mother...

538
01:01:12.687 --> 01:01:15.607
And made me what I am.

539
01:01:18.110 --> 01:01:21.029
And every time I take one
of those monsters out...

540
01:01:21.113 --> 01:01:24.407
I get a little piece of that life back.

541
01:01:24.491 --> 01:01:28.036
So don't you tell me about forgetting.

542
01:01:31.498 --> 01:01:33.058
Quinn: My fault?
He took us by surprise!

543
01:01:33.125 --> 01:01:35.961
Two of them against
your entire security force?

544
01:01:36.044 --> 01:01:38.338
Don't put that shit on me,
you were there too.

545
01:01:38.421 --> 01:01:41.633
I'm sure Deacon will appreciate
our cutback in payroll.

546
01:01:41.716 --> 01:01:45.011
- Quinn: Ow! You little skeez.
- The amputee lifestyle really suits you.

547
01:01:45.095 --> 01:01:47.222
I should put this stump
through that grin.

548
01:01:47.305 --> 01:01:50.809
Face it, angel. You were sloppy.
You got what you deserved.

549
01:01:55.188 --> 01:01:57.148
Quinn: Deac,
let me take this guy out, man.

550
01:01:57.232 --> 01:01:59.734
Look what he fucking did!
He took my hand again!

551
01:01:59.818 --> 01:02:02.571
Listen to me. I want him alive.

552
01:02:02.654 --> 01:02:04.489
Quinn: What the fuck are you talk...?

553
01:02:04.573 --> 01:02:07.826
You want him alive? We've been trying
to kill this motherfucker for years.

554
01:02:07.909 --> 01:02:09.744
Are you out of your fucking mind?
You want...?

555
01:02:09.828 --> 01:02:14.624
Shh. Big guy, relax.

556
01:02:14.708 --> 01:02:16.042
Be patient.

557
01:02:17.711 --> 01:02:19.171
We got a lot to do here.

558
01:02:20.630 --> 01:02:21.715
I need you, man.

559
01:02:25.677 --> 01:02:28.430
- I need you.
- Yeah.

560
01:03:10.889 --> 01:03:12.974
Frost: Good morning.

561
01:03:13.642 --> 01:03:15.769
How you feeling?

562
01:03:24.486 --> 01:03:26.446
Look at that.

563
01:03:29.324 --> 01:03:32.994
Ooh! Getting a little
toasty out here, huh?

564
01:03:34.412 --> 01:03:38.416
When was the last time you stopped
to appreciate a good sunrise?

565
01:03:38.500 --> 01:03:42.628
That's right, you were born a vampire,
so you never had the pleasure, have you?

566
01:03:42.712 --> 01:03:45.674
That's okay. It's all right.

567
01:03:45.757 --> 01:03:49.052
At least we're here together.
Share the moment.

568
01:03:49.135 --> 01:03:51.805
Which means a lot to me
by the way, really.

569
01:03:51.888 --> 01:03:53.807
I mean that.

570
01:03:55.392 --> 01:03:57.727
Because actually,
when you get to know me...

571
01:03:57.811 --> 01:04:00.689
I'm a fairly sentimental type of guy.

572
01:04:00.772 --> 01:04:03.608
Bit of an innocent, you might say.

573
01:04:05.401 --> 01:04:08.112
Do what you want, frost.

574
01:04:08.446 --> 01:04:10.407
Doesn't make any difference.

575
01:04:11.825 --> 01:04:14.786
You just don't fucking get it.

576
01:04:16.121 --> 01:04:19.124
- You're never gonna be a pureblood.
- Hold him.

577
01:04:21.876 --> 01:04:24.170
Dragonetti: You will never rule us.

578
01:04:25.463 --> 01:04:28.091
[Dragonetti groaning]

579
01:04:36.599 --> 01:04:39.853
Jesus Christ. Have a nice day.

580
01:04:40.562 --> 01:04:43.648
Sorry, you old dog. You just got
a little too long in the teeth.

581
01:04:43.732 --> 01:04:45.190
[Laughing]

582
01:04:45.275 --> 01:04:50.030
What, man? That was funny.
"Long, tooth." It's funny, man.

583
01:04:50.113 --> 01:04:52.657
Did I tell you the one
about the leprechaun...?

584
01:04:56.369 --> 01:04:58.163
[Screaming]

585
01:05:21.478 --> 01:05:24.064
What have you done with dragonetti?

586
01:05:30.653 --> 01:05:33.156
Let's get down to business, shall we?

587
01:05:33.239 --> 01:05:36.159
I need 12 volunteers.

588
01:05:42.749 --> 01:05:44.626
Blade: Whistler.

589
01:05:47.087 --> 01:05:48.380
Whistler: What is this?

590
01:05:50.006 --> 01:05:52.634
Smells like a vampire
wiped his ass with it.

591
01:05:52.717 --> 01:05:54.219
I took it from the archives.

592
01:05:54.302 --> 01:05:57.182
- Whistler: It's written in blood.
- Blade: It's from the book of erebus.

593
01:06:03.520 --> 01:06:05.939
I think it's what frost
has been working on.

594
01:06:06.022 --> 01:06:09.484
Whistler: It's something about
the blood god, the spirits of the 12.

595
01:06:09.567 --> 01:06:12.028
I don't know.
I can't make out the rest of it.

596
01:06:12.112 --> 01:06:13.696
Well, maybe this'll help.

597
01:06:14.614 --> 01:06:16.908
We'll figure out something.

598
01:06:17.617 --> 01:06:19.202
Blade: So, what's all of this?

599
01:06:19.285 --> 01:06:23.790
Took a trip to the hospital last night,
borrowed some equipment.

600
01:06:24.082 --> 01:06:26.751
For your miracle cure?

601
01:06:28.420 --> 01:06:31.214
Karen: This is edta.
It's an anticoagulant.

602
01:06:31.297 --> 01:06:33.425
We use it to treat blood clots.

603
01:06:34.467 --> 01:06:38.763
Look what happens when I introduce it
onto a sample of vampire blood.

604
01:06:40.473 --> 01:06:42.475
Take a step back.

605
01:06:42.559 --> 01:06:45.311
The reaction's energetic.

606
01:06:53.736 --> 01:06:57.782
- Some cure.
- Karen: I didn't say edta was a cure.

607
01:06:57.866 --> 01:07:02.412
But maybe you could use it
to explode some vampire heads.

608
01:07:04.372 --> 01:07:07.167
Wait a minute.
I need a sample of your blood.

609
01:07:07.250 --> 01:07:10.879
Later. I gotta go downtown.

610
01:07:10.962 --> 01:07:13.756
- I need some serum.
- Whistler: Serum can wait.

611
01:07:13.840 --> 01:07:16.259
This is important.

612
01:07:20.638 --> 01:07:22.432
[Coughing]

613
01:07:37.280 --> 01:07:40.241
- Is he sick?
- Cancer.

614
01:07:42.952 --> 01:07:45.705
You have a lot of love for him,
don't you?

615
01:07:45.788 --> 01:07:50.793
We have a good arrangement.
He makes the weapons, I use them.

616
01:07:54.714 --> 01:07:59.219
You know, my mother used to say,
"a cold heart is a dead heart."

617
01:08:16.986 --> 01:08:19.364
You don't look so good.

618
01:08:19.948 --> 01:08:25.453
I'm just a little tired.
You know, we've been working all night.

619
01:08:27.539 --> 01:08:30.500
I guess we didn't catch it in time.

620
01:08:31.417 --> 01:08:35.672
You got another day, two at the most.

621
01:08:39.467 --> 01:08:41.760
For what it's worth, I'm sorry.

622
01:08:42.679 --> 01:08:45.848
You make it sound like
I'm already dead.

623
01:09:03.658 --> 01:09:05.493
Frost: Blade.

624
01:09:29.350 --> 01:09:31.185
How you doing, chief?

625
01:09:32.645 --> 01:09:34.397
Easy.

626
01:09:35.356 --> 01:09:37.275
Wouldn't want our little friend here...

627
01:09:37.358 --> 01:09:40.111
To wind up on the back
of a milk carton, would we?

628
01:09:42.655 --> 01:09:47.160
It's nice to finally meet you, man.
Had my eye on you for years.

629
01:09:47.243 --> 01:09:52.290
I know all about you.
Your serum, whistler, everything.

630
01:09:52.790 --> 01:09:54.334
Sunblock.

631
01:09:54.417 --> 01:09:56.794
Hey, it's a start, right?

632
01:09:56.878 --> 01:10:00.506
The goal, of course, is to be like you.
A day Walker.

633
01:10:02.091 --> 01:10:04.177
You got the best of both worlds,
don't you?

634
01:10:05.136 --> 01:10:08.222
All our strengths,
none of our weaknesses.

635
01:10:09.015 --> 01:10:11.392
Well, maybe I don't see it that way.

636
01:10:11.476 --> 01:10:14.437
Oh, so it's back to pretending
we're human again?

637
01:10:14.520 --> 01:10:18.149
Come on.
Spare me the uncle Tom routine, okay?

638
01:10:18.232 --> 01:10:21.361
You can't keep denying
what you are, man.

639
01:10:22.153 --> 01:10:26.407
You think the humans will ever accept
a half-breed like you? They can't.

640
01:10:26.491 --> 01:10:28.701
They're afraid of you.

641
01:10:28.785 --> 01:10:31.579
And they should be.
You're an animal.

642
01:10:31.663 --> 01:10:33.581
You're a fucking maniac.

643
01:10:37.335 --> 01:10:40.463
Look at them. They're cattle.

644
01:10:40.546 --> 01:10:42.465
Pieces of meat.

645
01:10:42.548 --> 01:10:45.426
What difference does it make
how their world ends?

646
01:10:45.510 --> 01:10:49.806
Plague, war, famine.

647
01:10:49.889 --> 01:10:53.184
Morality doesn't even enter into it.

648
01:10:53.267 --> 01:10:58.189
We're just a function of natural
selection, man. The new race.

649
01:10:58.898 --> 01:11:01.359
Looks like your mascara's running.

650
01:11:08.700 --> 01:11:12.537
I'm offering you a truce.
I want you with us.

651
01:11:12.620 --> 01:11:15.415
What, do you think I'm stupid?

652
01:11:16.249 --> 01:11:18.084
[In foreign language]

653
01:11:23.297 --> 01:11:25.174
You're familiar with the blood god.

654
01:11:25.258 --> 01:11:27.510
[In English] Frost...

655
01:11:27.927 --> 01:11:30.555
You're nothing to me...

656
01:11:30.638 --> 01:11:33.599
But another dead vampire.

657
01:11:33.683 --> 01:11:36.352
You're an idiot, you know that?

658
01:11:36.436 --> 01:11:38.813
I came down here
offering you an easy way out...

659
01:11:38.896 --> 01:11:42.150
And you spit it right back
in my fucking face.

660
01:11:43.067 --> 01:11:44.777
Careful.

661
01:11:48.489 --> 01:11:50.783
What do I care?

662
01:11:50.867 --> 01:11:54.996
They're nothing but cattle,
just like you said.

663
01:11:55.538 --> 01:11:58.750
If you wanna take the hard road,
be my guest, pal.

664
01:11:58.833 --> 01:12:01.169
But I promise you,
by the time this is over...

665
01:12:01.252 --> 01:12:04.797
You're gonna wish they never cut you
from your mother's womb.

666
01:12:13.723 --> 01:12:15.516
[Screaming]

667
01:12:38.873 --> 01:12:40.166
Go home.

668
01:12:44.086 --> 01:12:46.631
It's simple.
Why do vampires need to drink blood?

669
01:12:46.714 --> 01:12:49.467
Because their own blood
can't sustain hemoglobin.

670
01:12:49.550 --> 01:12:52.553
Right. So it's a genetic defect
just like hemolytic anemia.

671
01:12:52.637 --> 01:12:55.348
That means that we have to treat it
with gene therapy.

672
01:12:55.431 --> 01:12:59.060
Rewrite the victim's DNA
with a retrovirus.

673
01:12:59.143 --> 01:13:01.312
They've been using it
on sickle-cell anemia.

674
01:13:01.395 --> 01:13:02.688
Are you sure that's safe?

675
01:13:02.772 --> 01:13:07.026
I have no idea,
but I don't have a choice, do I?

676
01:13:09.195 --> 01:13:11.030
You actually think this could work?

677
01:13:11.113 --> 01:13:14.909
On me? Yes.

678
01:13:15.159 --> 01:13:17.036
On blade, I'm not so sure.

679
01:13:17.119 --> 01:13:20.623
See, he didn't contract vampirism
from a bite like I did.

680
01:13:20.706 --> 01:13:24.544
He was born with it.
It's part of his DNA.

681
01:13:25.628 --> 01:13:29.173
I'm sure I can cure his thirst,
but it's gonna take time.

682
01:13:29.257 --> 01:13:31.801
We're out of time.

683
01:13:31.884 --> 01:13:34.720
You saw what was on that disk.

684
01:13:34.804 --> 01:13:37.223
[Quinn laughing]

685
01:13:39.308 --> 01:13:41.227
Damn.

686
01:13:42.186 --> 01:13:43.771
Get out of here.

687
01:13:59.579 --> 01:14:01.080
[Yells]

688
01:14:08.880 --> 01:14:10.423
I said, get out of here.

689
01:14:16.512 --> 01:14:19.932
Nice place. Took us a while to find it.

690
01:14:28.232 --> 01:14:31.027
- Bite me and get it over with.
- I ain't gonna bite you.

691
01:14:44.540 --> 01:14:46.584
Do your thing.

692
01:14:58.387 --> 01:15:00.264
Whistler?

693
01:16:07.289 --> 01:16:09.125
Frost took her.

694
01:16:16.924 --> 01:16:19.093
Listen to me.

695
01:16:21.470 --> 01:16:23.597
The disk...

696
01:16:23.848 --> 01:16:25.433
We decoded it.

697
01:16:25.933 --> 01:16:32.189
Frost is trying to trigger
a fucking vampire apocalypse.

698
01:16:34.400 --> 01:16:36.736
There's some kind of...

699
01:16:37.028 --> 01:16:40.906
Vampire god he's trying to resurrect.

700
01:16:41.699 --> 01:16:43.159
La magra.

701
01:16:46.704 --> 01:16:49.123
You're the key.

702
01:16:50.041 --> 01:16:51.625
He needs your blood.

703
01:16:55.379 --> 01:16:58.174
The blood of the day Walker.

704
01:17:00.468 --> 01:17:02.720
You're the chosen one.

705
01:17:06.307 --> 01:17:08.642
Listen to me, blade.

706
01:17:09.477 --> 01:17:12.813
- You can't go after him.
- Bullshit.

707
01:17:12.897 --> 01:17:18.235
If frost gets his hands on you,
it's all over.

708
01:17:20.529 --> 01:17:23.616
There'll be armies
of the motherfuckers.

709
01:17:25.910 --> 01:17:28.037
Shit.

710
01:17:31.957 --> 01:17:33.667
You're gonna have to finish me off.

711
01:17:35.336 --> 01:17:37.963
Don't want me coming back.

712
01:17:39.298 --> 01:17:40.883
We can treat the wounds.

713
01:17:42.676 --> 01:17:44.261
It's too far gone.

714
01:17:45.179 --> 01:17:47.556
You know that.

715
01:17:50.267 --> 01:17:52.436
Give me your gun.

716
01:17:54.313 --> 01:17:55.647
No.

717
01:17:57.024 --> 01:17:59.360
Give me the goddamn gun.

718
01:18:24.468 --> 01:18:28.138
Now walk away,
you stupid son of a bitch.

719
01:18:32.977 --> 01:18:35.312
Walk the fuck away.

720
01:18:44.530 --> 01:18:46.490
[Gunshot]

721
01:18:56.416 --> 01:19:00.044
By the time you watch this,
your friend whistler should be dead.

722
01:19:00.129 --> 01:19:03.382
If it makes any difference to you,
he put up quite a fight.

723
01:19:03.674 --> 01:19:06.760
You can find us
at the edgewood towers.

724
01:20:44.358 --> 01:20:46.819
You seem a bit tense.

725
01:20:46.902 --> 01:20:50.197
A bit pent-up maybe,
like you need to release something.

726
01:20:51.782 --> 01:20:57.037
No?
Blade not... giving it to you maybe?

727
01:20:58.289 --> 01:21:00.249
I don't know, I just...

728
01:21:00.791 --> 01:21:03.460
I see such a beautiful woman.

729
01:21:04.378 --> 01:21:06.630
Great skin.

730
01:21:08.507 --> 01:21:10.384
I'd like to see you happy, that's all.

731
01:21:10.467 --> 01:21:14.513
Is this the part
where you offer to turn me?

732
01:21:15.264 --> 01:21:17.725
Well, it's either that or a body bag.

733
01:21:18.225 --> 01:21:21.020
Go ahead. Bite me.

734
01:21:21.854 --> 01:21:24.064
I'll just cure myself.

735
01:21:24.148 --> 01:21:27.234
I did it before, and I can do it again.

736
01:21:27.318 --> 01:21:31.363
- There is no cure, baby.
- There is if you've been bitten.

737
01:21:31.739 --> 01:21:34.033
If you were once human.

738
01:21:39.455 --> 01:21:41.999
How'd you get that scar, Deacon?

739
01:21:42.082 --> 01:21:45.252
A born vampire would have the power
to regenerate from birth.

740
01:21:45.336 --> 01:21:48.422
You must've gotten scarred
before you were turned.

741
01:21:49.256 --> 01:21:50.966
Isn't that right?

742
01:21:51.050 --> 01:21:53.676
Vampires like you aren't a species.

743
01:21:53.761 --> 01:21:58.097
You're just infected, a virus,
a sexually-transmitted disease...

744
01:21:58.182 --> 01:22:00.392
I'll tell you what we are, sister.

745
01:22:00.476 --> 01:22:04.021
We're the top of the fucking food chain.
The blood god's coming...

746
01:22:04.104 --> 01:22:08.025
And after tonight,
you people are fucking history.

747
01:22:08.108 --> 01:22:11.820
He's a hurricane, an act of god.

748
01:22:11.904 --> 01:22:14.531
Anyone caught in his path
will instantly be turned.

749
01:22:16.575 --> 01:22:18.452
Everyone you've ever known...

750
01:22:18.535 --> 01:22:21.914
Everyone you've ever fucking loved.

751
01:22:21.997 --> 01:22:25.334
It won't matter who's pureblood
and who's not.

752
01:22:26.043 --> 01:22:28.962
How you gonna cure
the whole fucking world?

753
01:22:34.675 --> 01:22:37.053
And blade's blood is the key.

754
01:22:37.429 --> 01:22:38.847
We've got an intruder.

755
01:22:50.609 --> 01:22:52.319
[Elevator dings]

756
01:22:52.403 --> 01:22:55.322
[Motor revving]

757
01:23:06.750 --> 01:23:08.085
[Tires squealing]

758
01:23:08.168 --> 01:23:10.504
I don't think you understand.
This dude is bad.

759
01:23:10.587 --> 01:23:12.714
He had 20 guys around him...
I was there.

760
01:23:12.798 --> 01:23:15.551
- He's got shit he throws...
- He's got the sword and shit.

761
01:23:15.634 --> 01:23:19.179
Yeah, he can throw it in the air,
catch it underneath. Shut the fuck up!

762
01:23:19.263 --> 01:23:21.598
Man: [On radio] There's no
entrance or exits where we are.

763
01:23:21.682 --> 01:23:23.809
Make it happen, all right?
It's one guy on foot.

764
01:23:27.479 --> 01:23:29.189
Get him! Get him! Go!

765
01:23:29.273 --> 01:23:30.649
That's him, get him!

766
01:23:50.002 --> 01:23:52.713
Why am I hearing gunfire? Huh?

767
01:23:52.796 --> 01:23:55.883
Did I tell anybody to start shooting?
I need him alive.

768
01:23:56.633 --> 01:23:58.385
Man 1:

769
01:24:00.262 --> 01:24:03.182
Please. I just work for them.

770
01:24:05.726 --> 01:24:08.395
- Jesus Christ. Lock this place down.
- Man 2: Yes, sir.

771
01:24:45.390 --> 01:24:48.852
[Screaming]

772
01:25:56.044 --> 01:25:57.462
Eric?

773
01:26:09.057 --> 01:26:10.183
But you died.

774
01:26:11.434 --> 01:26:15.271
I came back, Eric.
That very same night.

775
01:26:17.316 --> 01:26:20.777
And Deacon welcomed me
into his arms.

776
01:26:27.826 --> 01:26:30.162
[Grunting]

777
01:26:36.543 --> 01:26:38.712
Jesus Christ.
I thought you'd be happy.

778
01:26:40.714 --> 01:26:44.051
You're finally being reunited
with your mother, and you act like this?

779
01:26:44.718 --> 01:26:46.595
Blade, give it up. It's over.

780
01:26:47.095 --> 01:26:49.598
She belongs to me, buddy.

781
01:26:51.808 --> 01:26:53.185
Don't look so surprised.

782
01:26:54.519 --> 01:26:58.023
You spent your whole life looking
for the vampire who bit your mother.

783
01:26:58.106 --> 01:26:59.983
Well, here I am.

784
01:27:02.736 --> 01:27:06.114
Who would have ever guessed
you'd survive your mother's death?

785
01:27:06.198 --> 01:27:09.159
But you did, and here we are...

786
01:27:09.242 --> 01:27:11.411
One big happy fucking family.

787
01:27:23.298 --> 01:27:25.759
I need my serum.

788
01:27:27.594 --> 01:27:30.931
Maybe when we get out of this,
I'll take that miracle cure of yours.

789
01:27:31.014 --> 01:27:32.641
Karen: There's one catch.

790
01:27:37.062 --> 01:27:38.438
If it works...

791
01:27:39.189 --> 01:27:44.027
You'll lose your strength
and your ability to regenerate.

792
01:27:44.568 --> 01:27:47.279
You'll be completely human.

793
01:28:07.801 --> 01:28:09.469
[Grunts]

794
01:28:24.693 --> 01:28:27.821
Come here. Get up, damn it.

795
01:28:49.092 --> 01:28:52.763
Frost: Blade, Karen,
glad you could make it.

796
01:28:52.846 --> 01:28:56.349
Hey, man. Thanks for the shades.

797
01:28:57.767 --> 01:29:02.062
Our ancestors called this place
the temple of eternal night.

798
01:29:04.900 --> 01:29:06.443
Nice, isn't it?

799
01:29:06.526 --> 01:29:10.071
Apparently,
these geniuses forgot it ever existed.

800
01:29:10.155 --> 01:29:12.365
Fortunately for us...

801
01:29:12.449 --> 01:29:17.120
I'm what you might call
a student of history.

802
01:29:30.008 --> 01:29:31.968
Why are we here?

803
01:29:34.345 --> 01:29:37.848
This temple was built
for one glorious moment:

804
01:29:37.933 --> 01:29:42.270
This night, for the blood god.

805
01:29:50.070 --> 01:29:51.947
Thanks.

806
01:29:56.076 --> 01:29:58.620
Let's see this sword of yours.

807
01:30:02.958 --> 01:30:05.877
Titanium, right? Acid-etched?

808
01:30:08.338 --> 01:30:10.257
I could get used to a weapon like this.

809
01:30:16.388 --> 01:30:19.975
What? You look surprised.

810
01:30:20.934 --> 01:30:23.854
I told you, blade,
I know everything about you.

811
01:30:25.146 --> 01:30:26.398
Hold out your arm, Quinn.

812
01:30:26.481 --> 01:30:28.817
Why, man?
Because they're, like, all better.

813
01:30:28.900 --> 01:30:32.237
Hold out your arm. Now.

814
01:30:34.990 --> 01:30:36.825
Quinn: Deac, I...

815
01:30:41.496 --> 01:30:43.081
Just kidding.

816
01:30:45.333 --> 01:30:48.420
He was fucking with me, man.
He was, like, fucking with me.

817
01:30:48.503 --> 01:30:50.213
Blade.

818
01:30:51.006 --> 01:30:53.133
- Blade.
- He can't hear you, honey.

819
01:30:53.216 --> 01:30:55.719
The thirst has got him now.

820
01:31:01.433 --> 01:31:02.642
What do we have here?

821
01:31:03.393 --> 01:31:05.353
The precious serum.

822
01:31:07.522 --> 01:31:12.068
How long's it been since you shot up?
Twelve, 13 hours maybe?

823
01:31:12.485 --> 01:31:15.572
I bet you're just dying for a drink,
aren't you?

824
01:31:18.366 --> 01:31:20.452
What's it feel like?

825
01:31:21.369 --> 01:31:23.204
Is your blood on fire?

826
01:31:23.872 --> 01:31:25.874
Try some.

827
01:31:26.207 --> 01:31:28.460
You might like it.

828
01:31:28.543 --> 01:31:31.004
Thanks, but I prefer the real thing.

829
01:31:32.047 --> 01:31:36.509
In any event, I don't think
you'll be needing these anymore.

830
01:31:43.266 --> 01:31:47.270
It's a shame, you know?
When I think of what you've become...

831
01:31:48.146 --> 01:31:50.065
What you should have become.

832
01:31:50.440 --> 01:31:53.902
I guess I don't blame you. I mean,
with everything that's happened...

833
01:31:53.985 --> 01:31:57.113
It's the human side of you
that's made you weak.

834
01:31:57.197 --> 01:32:01.326
- You should've listened to your blood.
- You can say what you want...

835
01:32:01.409 --> 01:32:04.329
But I promise you,
you'll be dead by dawn.

836
01:32:04.412 --> 01:32:06.039
Ooh.

837
01:32:06.122 --> 01:32:08.708
[Quinn laughing]

838
01:32:08.792 --> 01:32:10.209
Get him out of here.

839
01:32:14.631 --> 01:32:17.050
Get these fucks downstairs. Now.

840
01:32:17.133 --> 01:32:20.595
- Come on. Let's go. Let's go.
- Come on, now.

841
01:32:21.137 --> 01:32:22.430
Man: Come on.

842
01:32:25.141 --> 01:32:27.978
Don't worry, sweetheart.
We haven't forgotten about you.

843
01:32:28.061 --> 01:32:32.857
Oh, no, baby. We got something
real special planned for you.

844
01:32:32.941 --> 01:32:35.860
Quinn: Found me a surfer boy
with a nice ass and I sucked him dry.

845
01:32:35.944 --> 01:32:39.113
- And you'd figure he'd turn, right?
- But he didn't turn, did he?

846
01:32:39.197 --> 01:32:43.576
No, he turned into some kind of zombie.
It happens sometimes, cutie.

847
01:32:44.244 --> 01:32:46.955
- Quinn: He was fucking tripped out.
- Frost: Pathetic.

848
01:32:47.038 --> 01:32:49.916
Quinn: These guys are complete scum,
man. They'll eat anything.

849
01:32:50.000 --> 01:32:53.795
Animals, rodents, corpses,
and sometimes...

850
01:32:55.213 --> 01:32:56.673
They'll even eat vampires.

851
01:32:56.756 --> 01:32:58.091
That's a plus.

852
01:32:58.174 --> 01:33:02.345
And bearing that all in mind, I'd like
you to meet an old friend of yours.

853
01:33:03.346 --> 01:33:06.850
[Karen grunting]

854
01:33:07.642 --> 01:33:11.438
It's too bad. I kind of liked her.

855
01:33:12.105 --> 01:33:14.232
What a waste.

856
01:33:32.625 --> 01:33:34.544
[Curtis groans]

857
01:33:34.627 --> 01:33:37.547
Curtis: I don't know
what's happening to me.

858
01:33:37.630 --> 01:33:39.466
No pulse.

859
01:33:39.549 --> 01:33:42.719
And, of course,
there's the question of lividity.

860
01:33:44.387 --> 01:33:45.555
Guns?

861
01:33:50.560 --> 01:33:52.812
Karen?

862
01:33:53.229 --> 01:33:55.023
Karen.

863
01:33:55.106 --> 01:33:57.984
I never thought
I would see you again.

864
01:33:58.068 --> 01:34:01.488
Tell me, Karen, do you ever have
second thoughts about us?

865
01:34:05.575 --> 01:34:07.034
[Growls]

866
01:34:20.006 --> 01:34:21.549
Karen.

867
01:34:21.925 --> 01:34:23.802
Karen.

868
01:34:23.885 --> 01:34:25.303
Karen!

869
01:34:26.596 --> 01:34:29.057
Karen!

870
01:34:29.724 --> 01:34:30.850
Karen!

871
01:34:31.392 --> 01:34:32.936
Karen!

872
01:35:37.750 --> 01:35:40.295
You poor child.

873
01:35:41.504 --> 01:35:43.798
You're so sick.

874
01:35:44.424 --> 01:35:46.885
So thirsty.

875
01:35:46.968 --> 01:35:49.637
Don't touch me.

876
01:35:51.431 --> 01:35:54.684
Eric, look at me.

877
01:35:54.933 --> 01:35:59.396
Vampires are my people now.
I'm one of them.

878
01:35:59.772 --> 01:36:01.941
Can't be.

879
01:36:02.650 --> 01:36:05.111
Yes, it can.

880
01:36:07.238 --> 01:36:10.157
Try to understand, Eric.

881
01:36:10.992 --> 01:36:14.537
Your mother died a long time ago.

882
01:36:16.122 --> 01:36:18.374
I've hunted.

883
01:36:19.083 --> 01:36:21.377
I've killed.

884
01:36:23.171 --> 01:36:25.672
And I've enjoyed it.

885
01:36:26.216 --> 01:36:28.343
Haven't you?

886
01:36:29.135 --> 01:36:31.679
I know you have.

887
01:36:33.306 --> 01:36:37.560
Sooner or later, the thirst always wins.

888
01:37:21.562 --> 01:37:23.314
Come on.

889
01:37:29.237 --> 01:37:30.321
Spread them out.

890
01:37:31.364 --> 01:37:34.367
One on each glyph, under the tombs.

891
01:37:34.867 --> 01:37:36.202
Make it perfect.

892
01:38:17.284 --> 01:38:18.493
Frost: Bring the elevator up.

893
01:38:58.451 --> 01:39:00.370
Man: You stupid girl.

894
01:39:00.453 --> 01:39:04.040
What do you think is going to happen?
La magra? The blood god?

895
01:39:04.123 --> 01:39:07.418
That's nothing more than a fairy tale
for pretty little vampires.

896
01:39:07.502 --> 01:39:10.421
Then why are you sweating,
pureblood?

897
01:39:10.505 --> 01:39:13.091
Are you afraid
we're gonna steal your soul?

898
01:39:13.174 --> 01:39:15.635
Your pureblood spirit?

899
01:39:16.427 --> 01:39:19.305
You should be. Read the prophecy.

900
01:39:19.389 --> 01:39:22.600
It's time you fucks contributed
something to the cause.

901
01:39:26.813 --> 01:39:31.484
Even if frost is right,
you really think he cares about you?

902
01:39:31.567 --> 01:39:34.779
You're gonna die
just like the rest of us.

903
01:39:59.762 --> 01:40:01.722
Blade.

904
01:40:10.857 --> 01:40:13.651
Tonight, the age of man
comes to an end.

905
01:40:14.068 --> 01:40:15.945
No more compromises.

906
01:40:16.028 --> 01:40:17.488
We're gonna be gods.

907
01:40:19.073 --> 01:40:22.452
- Of course we are.
- Yeah.

908
01:40:23.744 --> 01:40:28.624
I'm gonna be naughty.
I'm gonna be a naughty vampire god.

909
01:40:31.878 --> 01:40:33.379
I'm right here.

910
01:40:36.507 --> 01:40:38.676
Gotta stop...

911
01:40:39.010 --> 01:40:42.180
- Stop the...
- Save your strength.

912
01:40:42.263 --> 01:40:44.098
Flow.

913
01:40:45.349 --> 01:40:48.269
You're hypovolemic.
You're bleeding to death.

914
01:40:48.852 --> 01:40:51.771
Need serum.

915
01:41:09.790 --> 01:41:11.584
Blade.

916
01:41:12.627 --> 01:41:14.253
Blade.

917
01:41:16.547 --> 01:41:18.549
Listen to me.

918
01:41:19.675 --> 01:41:22.512
I want you to take some of my blood.

919
01:41:23.721 --> 01:41:25.765
No.

920
01:41:27.600 --> 01:41:29.268
No.

921
01:41:29.560 --> 01:41:31.938
Look, just do it.

922
01:41:34.690 --> 01:41:36.400
[In foreign language]

923
01:41:57.588 --> 01:41:59.131
Is everybody thirsty?

924
01:41:59.924 --> 01:42:03.010
I hope you're all very fucking thirsty.

925
01:42:22.196 --> 01:42:25.324
Karen: Oh, please. Please, stop.

926
01:42:28.119 --> 01:42:29.954
Stop.

927
01:42:32.415 --> 01:42:33.499
Oh, god.

928
01:42:34.834 --> 01:42:36.919
Don't stop.

929
01:42:50.516 --> 01:42:52.768
Don't stop.

930
01:42:56.314 --> 01:42:58.149
Oh, god.

931
01:43:05.031 --> 01:43:06.616
[Yells]

932
01:43:44.320 --> 01:43:45.363
How was it?

933
01:44:29.407 --> 01:44:30.783
[Growling]

934
01:44:56.517 --> 01:45:00.855
Eric, I'm your mother.

935
01:45:02.773 --> 01:45:04.984
You wouldn't hurt your mother...

936
01:45:05.443 --> 01:45:07.319
Would you?

937
01:45:09.238 --> 01:45:11.157
Come here.

938
01:45:11.949 --> 01:45:14.118
It's you and me.

939
01:45:14.910 --> 01:45:17.163
I must release you.

940
01:45:17.538 --> 01:45:19.498
[Screaming]

941
01:45:28.132 --> 01:45:29.884
Fuck!

942
01:46:25.898 --> 01:46:29.151
[Grunting]

943
01:46:33.948 --> 01:46:36.575
- Mercury: Deacon?
- Frost: Not anymore.

944
01:46:52.466 --> 01:46:55.052
Frost.

945
01:46:55.135 --> 01:46:57.930
- Frost: Kill him.
- Wait. I owe you, man.

946
01:46:58.013 --> 01:46:59.640
I got two new hands, blade.

947
01:46:59.723 --> 01:47:02.434
I don't know which one to use
to kill you with.

948
01:47:16.782 --> 01:47:18.325
[Yells]

949
01:47:23.289 --> 01:47:24.331
Frost.

950
01:48:10.085 --> 01:48:11.754
Frost!

951
01:48:46.330 --> 01:48:48.290
I'm really going to enjoy this now.

952
01:49:37.006 --> 01:49:39.091
Frost: Hey, blade.

953
01:49:41.218 --> 01:49:42.428
Let's do this.

954
01:50:33.854 --> 01:50:36.148
[Mouths] What the fuck?

955
01:50:36.565 --> 01:50:38.859
You're too late, blade.

956
01:50:57.586 --> 01:50:59.379
My turn.

957
01:51:25.364 --> 01:51:27.825
Look at you. You're a little bitch.

958
01:51:29.618 --> 01:51:33.080
What, your serum?
Can't help you now, stud.

959
01:51:40.587 --> 01:51:42.631
Nice shot.

960
01:52:13.787 --> 01:52:18.167
Some motherfuckers
are always trying to ice skate uphill.

961
01:52:34.724 --> 01:52:37.226
[Screaming]

962
01:52:49.781 --> 01:52:51.366
Karen: Blade.

963
01:52:59.416 --> 01:53:01.752
Let's get out of here.

964
01:53:37.579 --> 01:53:41.667
I need to get back to the lab
if I'm gonna cure you.

965
01:53:42.584 --> 01:53:44.586
It's not over.

966
01:53:44.670 --> 01:53:46.838
You keep your cure.

967
01:53:47.172 --> 01:53:51.718
There's still a war going on,
and I have a job to do.

968
01:53:52.261 --> 01:53:56.890
You wanna help?
Make me a better serum.

969
01:54:34.010 --> 01:54:35.594
[Woman in Russian]:

970
01:54:36.722 --> 01:54:38.015
[Man in Russian]:

971
01:54:49.067 --> 01:54:51.361
[Man grunts and growls]

972
01:54:51.445 --> 01:54:53.864
[Speaking in Russian]

973
01:54:55.407 --> 01:54:57.284
[Blade speaks in Russian]

974
01:55:00.495 --> 01:55:01.747
[In Russian]

